name: Wave 3A — relation backing + active verb
description: ```
A relation declared with an evaluation backing (`Ownership is read from the
page's owner.`) plus a verb that names it (`to own`) makes an active-verb
condition (`the user owns the page`) lower deterministically to an identity
comparison on the backing property — no LLM, no per-call tool.
```
tags: inform7, wave3, relations, codegen

vocab_inline rel: ```
=== vocabulary ===
A user is a kind of thing.
A page is a kind of thing.
A page has an owner, which is a String.
Ownership relates one user to various pages.
Ownership is read from the page's owner.
The verb to own (it owns, it is owned) means the ownership relation.
```

source_inline: ```
---
name: verify
parameters: user, page
vocabulary: rel.merconfig
---

To verify a page for a user:
  if the user owns the page,
    complete with reason "ok".
```

expect_compile: pass
expect_no_unresolved:
expect_workflow_count: 1
expect_workflow_named: VerifyPage
expect_swift_contains: MeridianComparison.identifies(state.get("page.owner"), state.get("user"))
